Business Brief -- Imco Recycling Inc.:
   Firm Estimates Net Trailed
   Forecasts of Some Analysts
Imco said it expects full-year earnings to be comparable
to the figures for 1990, when Imco reported net income of
$5.7 million, or 53 cents a share, on revenue of $55 million.
   Despite decreased production early in the fourth quarter,
Ralph L. Cheek, chairman and chief executive officer, said
Imco plants in Morgantown, Ky., and Rockwood, Tenn., are
operating at capacity and are expected to continue to do so
through the first half of 1992.
   Imco stock was quoted at $9, unchanged, in late New York
Stock Exchange trading yesterday.